<meta name="description" content="&lt;p&gt;Susan Heathfield is a Human Resources expert. She is a management and organization development consultant who specializes in human resources issues and in management development to create forward thinking workplaces. Susan is also a professional facilitator, speaker, trainer, and writer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Susan is a member of the Society for Human Resource Management (SHRM). Susan contributes regularly to professional publications including a book chapter for &lt;em&gt;ASTD&lt;/em&gt; and a recent article in the &lt;em&gt;American Society for Quality&lt;/em&gt;&#39;s &lt;em&gt;Journal for Quality and Participation&lt;/em&gt;. This Web site is recommended as a resource by many colleges and universities including the ILR School Catherwood Library at Cornell University.&lt;/p&gt;
